content.description: First bolt is pretty far off the actual ground, can use small pro before you get to it.  This route is slabby goodness, but similar to the rest of the wall, needs a massive cleaning.  Moss carpet for most of the route.
content.location: Small ledge to the right of Old Dog New Tricks is a good start.

content.description: A clean slabby crack system on amazing rock.
content.protection: fingers to #2 camalot. chains at the top and slightly left.
content.location: Obvious clean cracks in the middle of the slab side.

climbs.name: Heel Boy
climbs.fa: Gordon Briody, Rob Waldsen, Vikto Kramar - 1993

content.description: This gorgeous sport route has interesting features.  Balancey ledges make this route a blast.
content.location: Far scramble down left of the "Old Dogs New Tricks" slab, right of main Dog Dome wall.  Interesting unfinished chimney project to the right.

content.description: A bizarre pocket of Vantage-style climbing in the middle of Leavenworth.  Located at the far-left wall of Dog Dome, this route really stands out.  Enjoyable 5.8 climbing, very dirty/mossy.  Bolted well.  Look for a spooky-old piton near the top!
content.location: Far left portion of Dog Dome.  If using the river crossing, just keep moving left at the wall.  If approaching via bridge trail, scramble down and left to get to the main wall, and keep moving left.
